UID:QMmTtoj0bJimyszJFGwYJ
SUMMARY:Know Your Rights Canvass
DTSTAMP:20260306T013341Z
DTSTART:20260305T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:In Seattle and across the country\\\, too many students and the
	ir families are afraid to be in public and to come to school. Some decide 
	to self-deport. Immigration enforcement is violating and restricting our r
	ights and creating a climate of fear. In Los Angeles\\\, Chicago\\\, and a
	cross the country\\\, educators have been on the frontline keeping their c
	ommunities safe from ICE activities. \\nSeattle Democratic Socialists of A
	merica\\\, educators\\\, and the broader community are also organizing to 
	combat this violence and fear by forming rapid response networks\\\, distr
	ibuting Know Your Rights information\\\, and more. Training and materials 
	will be provided!\n\nhttps://seattledsa.org/event/know-your-rights-canvass
	/\n\nFrom Seattle DSA
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/know-your-rights-canvass/
LOCATION:RSVP for details\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98122\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seattle-dsa
CATEGORIES:Seattle DSA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
