BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:o-bUj7e9U1BsghSErF3-7
SUMMARY:D3 Branch Meetup
DTSTAMP:20260306T013342Z
DTSTART:20260308T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:US/Israel WAR with Iran\\nWhere is it heading? What Should the 
	US Left & Socialists Call for?\\nThis Sunday\\\, Mar 8\\\, 5pm\\nVictrola 
	Cafe (411 15th Ave E) Community Room\\n  \\nThis past weekend Trump and Ne
	tanyahu unleashed hellfire on Iranians\\\, igniting a war that could spark
	 a broader\\\, regional conflagration.  And now Trump is not ruling out “b
	oots on the ground”. Infuriatingly\\\, the Democratic Party Establishment 
	has not come out with a full throated condemnation\\\, but rather has been
	 complaining about the process – of Trump not getting approval from Congre
	ss and for not making the case to Americans on the need for war.  However\
	\\, this avoids the question of whether they support the attacks or not. I
	t’s clear we cannot rely on the feckless pro-corporate Democratic Party es
	tablishment to mount an opposition to war and destruction. \\nWhere is thi
	s heading? How can we stop US imperialism? What should DSA representatives
	 say? What should the Left\\\, Unions\\\, and Socialists call for? What sh
	ould the Left/Socialists say about the Iranian regime? What are key demand
	s that Seattle DSA could raise in the anti-war movement? \\nJoin Seattle D
	SA District 3 branch members to discuss these important questions and thin
	k through what we can do in Seattle.  All are welcome! You DO NOT need to 
	live in District 3 to attend!\n\nhttps://seattledsa.org/event/us-israel-wa
	r-with-iran-where-is-it-heading-what-should-the-us-left-socialist-call-for
	/\n\nFrom Seattle DSA
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/us-israel-war-with-iran-where-is-it-headin
	g-what-should-the-us-left-socialist-call-for/
LOCATION:Victrola Coffee (411 15th Ave E)\\\, 411 15th Ave E\\\, Seattle\\\
	, WA\\\, 98112\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seattle-dsa
CATEGORIES:Seattle DSA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7eY8qEFYYZ7rB1FdmNyYB
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260306T013342Z
DTSTART:20260308T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-03
	-08T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-03-08T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
