	ves the members of Seattle DSA. During these short weekly check-ins\\\, LC
	 members will primarily be ensuring work is on track\\\, though pressing b
	usiness may occasionally be discussed and voted on. Members are welcome to
	 observe LC meetings by RSVPing here. \\nThe LC has an informal check-in m
	eeting every Tuesday (except the fourth Tuesday of the month for the GMMs)
	 from 7:00pm – 7:45pm over Zoom. \\nIf there’s something specific you’d li
	ke to bring to the Local Council\\\, please fill out the LC Request Form w
	hich can be found on the private resources page of our website. \\nIf you 
	are a member that has not yet been added to our Slack (which is required t
	o log in to the private resources page)\\\, you can request to be added he
	re. \\nPlease note that on rare occurrences\\\, LC meetings will be cancel
	led due to holidays or unusual circumstances and these changes may not alw
	ays be reflected on this calendar — if you show up to the meeting and aren
	’t let in after 5 minutes\\\, that is almost certainly what has happened.\
	n\nhttps://seattledsa.org/event/local-council-meeting-6-2/2026-03-17/\n\nF
	rom Seattle DSA
